The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Winning start by Thailand

 - ASIAN HOPMAN CUP 

Hyderabad: Thailand made a winning start to their Asian Hopman Cup campaign, defeating Philippines 2-1 in group B on Friday. 

Nudnida Luangnam beat Czarina Arevalo 6-4, 6-4 in the womens match, while Weerapat Doakmaiklee overcame Patrick Tierro 6-7, 6-3 7-5 in the mens contest. 

The Filipino pair then won the mixed doubles 6-3, 6-4. 

Thailand face Taiwan on Saturday to decide who goes through to the final as group winners. 

China beat Japan 2-1 to keep alive slim hopes of qualifying for the final from group A. Shuai Zhang defeated Tomoko Yonemura 6-3, 4-6, 6-4 before Yuichi Sugita helped Japan draw level with a 6-1, 6-3 victory over Mao-Xin Gong in the mens match. 

The Chinese pair then won the mixed doubles 6-0 6-1. 

Hosts India play Japan on Saturday. (Reuters) 




